---
---
<section id="technology" class="py-32 bg-[#050505] relative border-t border-zinc-900">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
            
            <!-- Tech Details -->
            <div>
                <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6 tracking-tight font-serif">The AI Director</h2>
                <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xl mb-10 leading-relaxed">
                    Ashbend isn't railroaded. A background Narrative Director constantly watches the village state. If nothing interesting happens, it nudges the world.
                </p>
                
                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <div class="relative pl-8 border-l border-zinc-800 pb-8">
                        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-amber-600 rounded-full -left-[6.5px] top-1"></div>
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Memory Stream</h4>
                        <p class="text-zinc-400">NPCs don't just prompt a massive context window. They observe the world and retrieve relevant memories via GraphRAG to formulate their next move.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="relative pl-8 border-l border-zinc-800 pb-8">
                        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-amber-600 rounded-full -left-[6.5px] top-1"></div>
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Social Propagation</h4>
                        <p class="text-zinc-400">Rumors spread organically. Mira hears about the demon scout -> Mira tells Tovan -> Tovan confronts Lysa. The social web evolves without you.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="relative pl-8 border-l border-transparent">
                        <div class="absolute w-3 h-3 bg-amber-600 rounded-full -left-[6.5px] top-1"></div>
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Consequences</h4>
                        <p class="text-zinc-400">Quests have a deterministic aftermath. Finishing a task branches into trusted, wary, or neutral memories that permanently unlock new cutscenes or doors.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Visual Showcase -->
            <div class="relative">
                <div class="relative rounded-sm overflow-hidden border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900 shadow-2xl group">
                    <img src="/assets/bridge_whisper.jpg" alt="The Bridge Whisper" class="w-full h-auto object-cover opacity-80 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500" />
                    
                    <div class="absolute bottom-4 right-4 bg-zinc-950/90 border border-zinc-800 p-4 rounded-sm backdrop-blur-md max-w-[300px]">
                        <p class="text-xs font-mono text-zinc-500 mb-2">> memory_retrieval_active</p>
                        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono">
                            <span class="text-amber-500">Tovan:</span> "Mira mentioned you were asking about the forest. After the demon scout reports, I don't trust anyone wandering out there."
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
